cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.NE 

This paper proposes a new graph convolution operator for Graph Neural Networks (GNNs) that models interactions between neighbor nodes. The paper focuses on improving the representation ability of GNNs for semi-supervised node classification tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) since GNNs have been widely used in these areas. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of natural language processing (NLP) datasets, indicating a possible connection to cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper's focus on improving the representation ability of GNNs suggests a possible connection to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
